    • runProgram

      @RequestMapping(value="/executeProgram", params="special_token") @ResponseBody public java.lang.String runProgram​(@RequestParam("special_token") java.lang.String special_token) throws java.io.IOException
      runProgram() 
       This is the driver of the program. It creates the necessary 4 TeamDynamix Tickets per 1 appointment.

 In order the driver does the following....

 1. Set-up
    a. Check if a valid special_token was given.
    b. Check if today is a weekday.
    c. Get the appointment start times from the GoogleSheet specified by the SPREADSHEET_ID
    d. Initialize the TeamDynamix object

 2. Begin the Thread
    a. Place the start times into their own array
    b. Format the start times into the format specified by TeamDynamix found here
    c. Create 4 tickets per 1 appointment time.

 3. Return a message to the requesting party.
      Parameters:
      special_token - A token in the request URL indicating an authorized request
      Returns:
      A message indicating that the program has started.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - If getting the values from the GoogleAPI fails.
